The '''Kohler family of Wisconsin''' is a family notable for its prominence in business, [[Socialite|society]], and politics in the US state of [[Wisconsin]]  during the 19th, 20th and 21st centuries.<ref>{{cite web|title=The World's Billionaires|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/herbert-kohler-jr/|publisher=Forbes|accessdate=27 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The 10 Most Generous Families|url=http://www.townandcountrymag.com/society/most-generous-families#slide-1|publisher=Town and Country Magazine|accessdate=27 March 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Fossedal|first=Gregory A.|title=Kohler: A Political Biography of Walter J. Kohler, Jr|date=2003|publisher=Transaction Publishers|isbn=0-7658-0192-2}}</ref> Its members include two [[Governor of Wisconsin|Governors of Wisconsin]], and the founder and executives of [[Kohler Co.]], a Wisconsin-based manufacturing and hospitality company.

