{{refimprove|date=January 2017}} '''New York's 25th State Senate district''' is one of 63 districts of the [[New York State Senate]]. It is currently represented by Senator [[Velmanette Montgomery]] (D),<ref>{{cite web|title=Velmanette Montgomery|url=http://www.nysenate.gov/senator/velmanette-montgomery/bio|website=nysenate.gov|accessdate=29 June 2015|ref=velmanette-montgomery-bio}}</ref> who was elected in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=NYS Board of Elections Senate Election Returns Nov. 6, 2012|url=http://www.elections.ny.gov/NYSBOE/elections/2012/General/SD_07292013.pdf|website=elections.ny.gov|accessdate=29 June 2015}}</ref>
==District profile== District 25 is made up of [[Brooklyn]] neighborhoods including [[Fort Greene]], [[Boerum Hill]], [[Red Hook (Brooklyn)|Red Hook]], [[Bedford-Stuyvesant]], [[Sunset Park, Brooklyn|Sunset Park]], [[Gowanus]], and [[Park Slope]].<ref>{{cite web|title=District 25, New York State Senate|url=http://www.nysenate.gov/district/25|website=nysenate.gov|accessdate=29 June 2015|ref=district-map}}</ref>
==Past senators== * [[Daniel Squadron]] (2009-2013) * [[Martin Connor]] (1978 - 2009) * [[Carol Bellamy]] (1972-1978) * [[Manfred Ohrenstein]] (1966-1970; redistricted to District 27) * ? (1965-1966) * [[Manfred Ohrenstein]] (1964-1965) * [[John D. Farrell]] ( - 1964)
